		<div id="comment_body_65512376"><p>We hear  so much these days about young urban hipsters deciding not to have children because the world as they see it appears to be coming to an end. But when I visited Iowa this month, I was impressed by by seeing babies everywhere. So if children represent optimism about the future, look at these differences among states:</p><p><a href="https://worldpopulationreview.com/state-rankings/birth-rate-by-state" title="worldpopul...review.com">https://worldpopulationreview....</a> [worldpopul...review.com]</p><p>Now consider the effects, long-term, of these differentials on our culture and politics.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_65512376">
